727445f.text:
Myrtle Ave., west of Woodhaven Boulevard, showing in the foreground . bridge over a division right of way of the Long Island Railroad.
September 8, 1933.
Trvin Fitterman.

727446f.text:
Myrtle Avenue, east from Woodhaven Boulevard, showing the thoroughfare entering Forest Park after crossing the small bridge over the Long Island Railroad tracks.
Trvin Fitterman
727446f.folder: Myrtle Avenue & Woodhaven Boulevard, Queens, NY

727447f-a.text:
Myrtle Ave. (tracks thereon), at the S.W. corner of Woodhaven Boulevard (formerly Trotting Course Lane), showing the former Eldorado Roadhouse built by one Koenig in what was Koenig Park. One Nammerer was the owner in 1891. This place was still standing in 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
